      "content": "hey, im working on this embedded c++ project and the heap just keeps growing till it crashes. i think there is a leak somewhere in this loop. can u take a look?\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n\nvoid processData(int size) {\n    int* buffer = new int[size];\n    for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i) {\n        buffer[i] = i * 2;\n    }\n    \n    // logic to process buffer...\n    std::cout << \"Processed \" << size << \" elements.\" << std::endl;\n    \n    // i think i'm supposed to clean up here?\n}\n\nint main() {\n    for (int i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {\n        processData(1024);\n    }\n    return 0;\n}\n```",
